org.patrodyne.timer.httptask

Class HttpTaskServlet

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.servlet.GenericServlet
      • javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet
        • org.patrodyne.timer.httptask.HttpTaskServlet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, javax.servlet.Servlet, javax.servlet.ServletConfig

    public class HttpTaskServlet
extends javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet
    A servlet to initiate Timer managed tasks and invoke HTTP endpoints on a periodic schedule. Tasks are configured from properties provided at the JNDI path, java:comp/env/timer/httptask. Each JDNI property provides a key (job name) and value TYPE|DELAY|PERIOD|URL where TYPE = FD (fixed delay) or FR (fixed rate) DELAY = initial offset in milliseconds PERIOD = time between invocations in milliseconds URL = an HTTP endpoint.
    Author:
    Rick O'Sullivan
